Let $x$ be any set. Using ZFC axioms, how to show $(x,x)=\{\{x\}\} 
eq x$? Similar question: $ igcup x 
eq x?$ Solved questions: $x 
eq P(x)$ ($x$ is a subset of $x$ but $x 
otin x$ by the Foundation axiom) $\{x\}=\{x,x\}
eq x$ (by the Foundation axiom)

